cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.AI

The paper presents a new machine learning algorithm for IoT Big Data, specifically for learning decision trees in a distributed streaming setting. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of Apache SAMOA, a platform for mining distributed data streams, which suggests a possible fit with cs.DB (Databases) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
